    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Colorful, multilayered appliqué panels created by the Cuna Indians and usually applied to the front or back of women's blouses.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
